To run this program you need to install the library WxWidgets 3.0

link : https://sites.google.com/site/opensourceconstriubtions/ettl-martin-1/tutorials/how-to-install-wxwidgets-on-a-linux-system

________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________

The compilation takes place in 2 stages:

1 ---  g++ -c `wx-config --cppflags` main.cpp Piece.cpp GamePanel.cpp Frame.cpp InfoPanel.cpp Opponents.cpp SelectOpponentsPanel.cpp Server.cpp StartDialog.cpp GamePanelOpponent.cpp Board.cpp `wx-config --libs`

2 ---  g++ -o tetris `wx-config --cppflags` main.o Piece.o GamePanel.o Frame.o InfoPanel.o Opponents.o SelectOpponentsPanel.o Server.o StartDialog.o GamePanelOpponent.o Board.o `wx-config --libs`

To run:

./tetris